China’s Huaneng Power First-Half Unit Fuel Costs Rise 8.4%

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-08-10T10:18:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-10/china-s-huaneng-power-first-half-unit-fuel-costs-rise-8-4-1-.html
Huaneng Power International Inc. (902) , a
unit of  China ’s largest electricity producer, said its unit fuel
costs gained 8.4 percent in the first half from a year earlier.  Costs rose to 263.7 yuan ($41) per megawatt-hour, Chief
Accountant Zhou Hui said on a conference call today. Forty-two
percent of the company’s 38 plants in China recorded losses
during the six-month period, she said.  The cost of standard coal with a calorific value of 7,000
kilocalories per kilogram increased 9.6 percent from a year
earlier to 844.1 yuan a metric ton, excluding taxes, Zhou said.  --Winnie Zhu. Editors: Ryan Woo.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Winnie Zhu in Shanghai at 
 wzhu4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
